description: Bloomberg’s Riley Ray Griffin joins Morning Joe to break down Kamala Harris’s digital campaign success, highlighting how she turned Biden’s failed meme strategy into a viral hit. By leaning into Republican attacks, using TikTok effectively, and amplifying her message through influencers, Harris has managed to dominate social media with a rapid response strategy.
title: Kamala Harris rides viral meme 'wave' as campaign seizes organic momentum

description: A top Democrat wants the federal cybersecurity agency CISA to ramp up help for state and local election officials facing an onslaught of disinformation.
title: Top Democrat urges Biden admin to do more to help local election officials fight a flood of disinformation

description: After making landfall as a Category 4 hurricane in Florida, Helene caused significant damage in the Big Bend region, but the full extent is still unknown. NBC News' Marissa Parra breaks down what we know about the storm's destruction so far.
title: Full extent of damage from Helene is still unknown but could be 'catastrophic'

description: Tallahassee Mayor John Dailey speaks with NBC News' Gadi Schwartz about the city's preparation and security as Hurricane Helene is about to make history as the first Category 4 hurricane to hit Florida.
title: 'Tallahassee strong': Mayor speaks of city's preparation as Hurricane Helene approaches

description: Videos show Florida being battered by heavy wind, rain and massive floods as the state prepares for Hurricane Helene's landfall.
title: Videos show heavy wind and rain as Florida braces for Hurricane Helene
